    <h2 style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
     <span style="font-weight: 400">
      <font face="Arial">
       American Sign Language:  "now"
      </font>
     </span>
    </h2>
    <blockquote>
     <span style="font-weight: 400">
      <font face="Arial">
       <hr color="#000000" size="1"/>
       <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
        Also see:
        <a href="../t/today.htm">
         TODAY
        </a>
       </p>
       <hr color="#000000" size="1"/>
       <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
        <br/>
        NOW:
        <br/>
        Move the "Y" hands down a few inches.
Your palms should be facing upward.
        <br/>
        Note: If you use a double motion on this version of the sign for now, it can 
  be interpreted as TODAY.
        <br/>
        <br/>
        <img border="0" src="/images/now.gif" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto" width="480"/>
        <iframe allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/g2j70neQ_lI?rel=0" width="560">
        </iframe>
       </p>
       <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
        <img border="0" height="230" src="/images/now1.jpg" width="244"/>
        <img border="0" height="230" src="/images/now2.jpg" width="244"/>
        <img border="0" height="230" src="/images/now3.jpg" width="244"/>
       </p>
       <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
       </p>
       <hr color="#000000" size="1"/>
       <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
        <br/>
        NOW (old version)
        <br/>
        Another version of the sign NOW/CURRENT/presently 
is made by placing both of your hands in front of you.
        <br/>
        Each hand should be bent upward.
        <font size="+1">
         <br/>
         Note:
        </font>
        Most people prefer to use the "y" handshape.
        <br/>
        Sharply drop both hands a short distance.
        <br/>
        <img height="158" src="/images/present.gif" width="239"/>
        <img border="0" height="234" src="/images/nowb1.jpg" width="224"/>
        <img border="0" height="234" src="/images/nowb2.jpg" width="224"/>
        <br/>
       </p>
       <hr color="#000000" size="1"/>
       <p align="left" style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
        <br/>
        "TODAY" (version) / "right now" [NOW+NOW]
        <br/>
        The meaning of this sign depends on what the other person asked. For example, 
  if the other person asks you what time is the meeting?  If you respond "NOW+NOW" 
  it would mean "right now" or currently.
        <br/>
        If someone asks you what day the party is, you can respond by signing "NOW + 
  NOW."
        <br/>
        The double "NOW" is interpreted to mean "today."
        <br/>
        <img border="0" src="/images/now-now-today.gif" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto" width="480"/>
        <img border="0" height="221" src="/images/now.ht28.jpg" width="254"/>
        <img border="0" height="221" src="/images/now.ht29.jpg" width="254"/>
        <img border="0" height="221" src="/images/now.ht28.jpg" width="254"/>
        <img border="0" height="221" src="/images/now.ht29.jpg" width="254"/>
        <br/>
       </p>
